   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Safe Mode Tutorial (Notebook)\n",
    "\n",
    "Run the baseline benchmark, safe smoke scenario, and inspect SafeSwitch telemetry directly from a notebook environment."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Baseline agentic run\n",
    "Ensure \`orchid_ranker\` is installed with the \`agentic\` extra and this notebook is executed from the repo root so \`PYTHONPATH=src\` resolves correctly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%%bash\n",
    "set -euo pipefail\n",
    "PYTHONPATH=src python benchmarks/run_agentic_ml100k.py \\\n",
    "  --rounds 2 --top-users 40 --top-items 80 --top-k 6 --dim 8 \\\n",
    "  --log-dir runs/tutorial-baseline-notebook --quick"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Safe smoke scenario\n",
    "This uses the helper script (adaptive-only, 60×120 slice, 5 rounds)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%%bash\n",
    "set -euo pipefail\n",
    "./scripts/run_ml100k_safe_smoke.sh runs/tutorial-safe-notebook"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Inspect SafeSwitch telemetry\n",
    "The following cell loads the adaptive JSONL log and tabulates the gate metrics per round."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import json\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "log_path = Path('runs/tutorial-safe-notebook/adaptive.jsonl')\n",
    "rows = []\n",
    "for line in log_path.read_text().splitlines():\n",
    "    obj = json.loads(line)\n",
    "    if obj.get('type') == 'round_summary':\n",
    "        gate = obj.get('safe_gate') or {}\n",
    "        rows.append({\n",
    "            'round': obj.get('round'),\n",
    "            'serve_policy': gate.get('serve_policy'),\n",
    "            'p_used': gate.get('p_used'),\n",
    "            'p_next': gate.get('p'),\n",
    "            'uplift_lcb': gate.get('lcb'),\n",
    "            'accept_lcb': gate.get('acc_lcb'),\n",
    "        })\n",
    "pd.DataFrame(rows)
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Plot mix probability vs. rounds\n",
    "This visualization highlights when the gate allows the student to serve."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(6, 3))\n",
    "plt.plot(df['round'], df['p_next'], marker='o')\n",
    "plt.title('SafeSwitch mix probability')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Round')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('p (probability of adaptive)')\n",
    "plt.ylim(0, 1)\n",
    "plt.grid(True)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
 ],
